I've updated the gist at https://gist.github.com/1c4bffaf558fbec5bf7b6de98009968b to simplify it somewhat. It now doesn't need any interaction with IPC or events. This is enough to trigger the leak:

```js
// preload.js
let g_fn = null

contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld("test", {
  on: (fn) => g_fn = fn,
});

setInterval(() => {
  if (g_fn)
    g_fn(function() {})
})

// renderer.js
window.test.on(() => {});
```

Just sending a function back over the bridge results in leaks.
